This Program was created for research purposes at Kansas State University by Erick Saenz under the supervision of Dr.Hsu and in collaboration with Dr. Scott Dietrich

The overall goal of this project is as follows:
   Accurately measure tackling proficiency amoung youth by the Standardized Assessment of Tackling Technique (SATT) with Machines (Computer Vision)
   
   The SATT3 rubric is found under Notes/Spread_Sheets/

The subgoals to accomplish this goal are as follows:
  0) Identify a player before they tackle accurately   <--- (Currently Working on this)
  Measure:
  1) PC - Player Control 
  2) HET - Head Eye Torso Position 
  3) SZ - Strike Zone 
  4) Ascending Hit /Upward Arm Rips
  5) Leg Drive 
  
 
All python files should be able to run independently. 
REQUIREMENTS: (PIP install)
OPENCV installed  (v4.1.1.26) -->(pip install opencv-python)
imutils installed (v0.5.3)
numpy installed (v1.17.2)
pytube installed (v9.5.2)
